        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-01-08 15:23:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6: Code-Review-2\n\nThis whole ticket is not acceptable for me. In short, there are to many not specific changes for one commit. As I suppose, this is general code refactoring, and almost whole class is changed. What is more, unit tests are also changed, so I am even not sure if old tests passed for this new implementation. All this makes the pathset completely unreadable. This is my suggestion:\n\n1. Try do divide your improvements into smaller pieces that can be described, for example -> introducing lambda's where possible, and so on. Then make a gerrit ticket. The key point here is to provide gerrit ticket with changes that are easy to understand, it should be also described in ticket comment. \n2. Do not change existing tests to prove that they passed for new changes. You can refactor them later, in another ticket or next pathset.",
        "patchset_number": 6
