        "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n(9 comments)\n\nŁukasz,\nI don't quite understand the statement \"there are to many not specific changes for one commit\". It is nothing more than a simple refactor, which didn't change the logic. If you could point out the places where the logic has changed I would be really grateful as it wasn't my intention.\nI had to move some entire functions to tidy them up, so multiple lines modifications are inevitable.\nI can split the commit in two parts: \n- BBInputSetupUtils.java in one review\n- BBinputSetupUtilsTest.java in another\nIntroducing more changes would waste not only my time, but also the time of the reviewers who made the effort to read the review. (Their comments and the review history will be lost anyway)",
